mhrs_us.dat     Sources: 
                John W. Kendrick (1961)
                Productivity Trends in the United States.
                Princeton, NJ: Princeton University Press.
                Table A-X. National Economy: Manhours, by Major Sector,
                1869-1957 (millions), pp. 311-13 for years 1869-1947.

                John W. Kendrick (1973)
                Postwar Productivity Trends in the United States, 1948-1969.  
                New York, NY: National Bureau of Economic Research.
                Table A-10. National Economy: Manhours by Sector,
                1948-1966 (millions), p. 226.

                Columns: (1)  Year
                         (2)  Total manhours (incl. military)
                         (3)  _ civilian economy
                         (4)  _ general government
                         (5)  ___ military 
                         (6)  ___ civilian
                         (7)  _ private economy
                         (8)  ___ farm
                         (9)  ___ nonfarm

                       NOTE:  (7)     After 1948, add business + households
                              (9)     After 1948, add nonfarm + households


